                        <h1 id="main-content">Using Font Awesome Pro with NDS (NPM)</h1>
                        
                        <p><strong>Updated:</strong> December 9, 2020</p>

                        <h2>Overview</h2>
                        <p>NIAID Design System (NDS) users automatically have access to the free version of <a href="https://fontawesome.com/">Font Awesome</a>, the official icon library of NDS. If you have been granted access to the paid <a href="https://fontawesome.com/pro">Font Awesome Pro</a> version by OCGR, or are planning to purchase and incorporate Pro into your NDS site yourself, this guide will detail the steps involved using the Node Package Manager (NPM) approach.</p>

                        <hr>

                        <h2>Obtaining Your License Key</h2>

                        {% include "@nds/02-molecules/components/component-media/_component-media-main.twig" with
                            {
                                "component_media_src": 'font-awesome-pro/fa-account-details.png',
                                "component_media_alt": 'See caption for details',
                                "component_media_credit": 'NIAID',
                                "component_media_caption": 'Find your account details below your personal information on the Font Awesome website.',
                                "component_media_lightbox": "yes",
                                "component_media_float": "right"
                            }
                        %}

                        <p>The first step in integrating Font Awesome Pro into your site is adding a license file containing your Pro account license key.</p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>Login to your Font Awesome account.</li>
                            <li>Click on the profile icon in the top right of the site.</li>
                            <li>Select "Account Details" below your personal information.</li>
                        </ol>

                        <p>Your license key will be under a section named "Pro npm Package Token."</p>

                        {% include "@nds/02-molecules/components/component-media/_component-media-main.twig" with
                            {
                                "component_media_src": 'font-awesome-pro/package-token.png',
                                "component_media_alt": 'See caption for details',
                                "component_media_credit": 'NIAID',
                                "component_media_caption": 'The location of your Font Awesome license key.',
                                "component_media_lightbox": "yes"
                            }
                        %}

                        <h2>Creating a License File</h2>

                        {% include "@nds/02-molecules/components/component-media/_component-media-main.twig" with
                            {
                                "component_media_src": 'font-awesome-pro/npmrc.png',
                                "component_media_alt": 'See caption for details',
                                "component_media_credit": 'NIAID',
                                "component_media_caption": 'The location to place your .npmrc file.',
                                "component_media_lightbox": "yes",
                                "component_media_float": "right"
                            }
                        %}

                        <ol>
                            <li>Open your project repository in your preferred code editor.</li>
                            <li>Create a new file named <strong>.npmrc</strong> in the same folder where your package.json file resides.</li>
                            <li>Paste the following code in this new .npmrc file:</li>
                        </ol>

                        <code>
                            @fortawesome:registry=https://npm.fontawesome.com/
                            //npm.fontawesome.com/:_authToken=XXXXXXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXX
                        </code>

                        <p>Replace "XXXXXXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXX" with your license key.</p>

                        <h2>Installing Font Awesome Pro with NPM</h2>

                        <p>With your .npmrc file created, run the following command to install the Font Awesome Pro Node module:</p>

                        <code>
                            npm install --save @fortawesome/fontawesome-pro
                        </code>

                        <p>The installed Node module is named @fortawesome.</p>

                        <h2>Copying Webfonts &amp; Modifying the SCSS File</h2>

                        <p>Now that the Font Awesome Pro Node module is installed, you can utilize the accompanying font files in your SCSS.</p>
                        
                        <p>To start, copy the files in the @fortawesome/fontawesome-pro/webfonts folder from within the Node module and paste the files inside your source/webfonts/ directory under font-awesome/. You may hit "Replace" if you receive a notification about duplicate Font files.</p>

                        <p>Navigate to the style.scss file in source/css/. Add the following line below the Font Awesome import statements starting on line 6:</p>

                        <code>
                            @import "../../node_modules/@fortawesome/fontawesome-pro/scss/light";
                        </code>

                        {% include "@nds/02-molecules/components/component-media/_component-media-main.twig" with
